Face it, those who know of a good drop rate, will not directly state where it is for fear of it becoming perma camped.  <br>
<br>
There are 2 undisputable ways to get the info from them.<br>
<br>
1.  Hunt where they SCREAM not to, cause drop rates totally blows there (which they would be screaming to keep you away from &quot;their&quot; drop spots).<br>
<br>
2.  Get their toons name and server /who all greedyl33twhore004, if they aren't anon then you know what zone to head to, if they are anon, you have a couple choices.<br>
<br>
  a.  Zone by zone search for them<br>
  b. send them a /tell and ask for help at xxplanarcamp, buff etc etc etc, they will generally respond with WTF I am in PoXXX nowhere near where your crappy group is.<br>
  c.  if they are in a guild do a /who all &quot;guild&quot; one of which will more than likely not be anon, send a tell to the persons guildmate and either accuse them of something (like stealing your camp), or play nice and creative in an attempt to see if guildie004 is with them and if so where you might find them.<br>
  d.  Send person a tell, &quot;hey I just got my 3rd 62 pet, you happen to need it and/or want to trade a spell for it? <br>
  e.  Send them a tell, wow I have gotten 20 parchments in the past hour, how about I bring my dup's to you since I won't need them.<br>
<br>
d and e will probably result in the person wanting to &quot;share&quot; drop spots with you, now how hard would it be for you to mention bogus spots in exchange for good spots?<br>
