<br>
They should be dropping at the same frequency as you would get in say SkyFire for spells.<br>
<br>
They drop frequently, and at times rarely, but in any event in enough numbers people feel they have a shot at their spells by the end of a evening's play time.<br>
<br>
The way PoP is laid out from what we are seeing, if your in a top tier guild, Verant made it so you can progress faster to the 2nd/3rd level zones easiest because of the gear you farmed and parchments drop a plenty, but the rest of us are screwed and FIGHTING each other for the meager drops, and locations they do drop, if your lucky enough to find any.<br>
<br>
Nice way to say thank you to your player base, go out and be mad as hell when the one or 2 locations where even one parchment dropped is fought over.<br>
<br>
Not the way the game should be played in my opinoin.<br>
<br>
Scatter them about, so any mob may have one, put more on higher level mobs, and even more on mini boss's.<br>
<br>
That doesn't mean every mini boss or higher mob will always have one, but the chances are great they will.<br>
<br>
The same with regualar mobs. You see them often enough to feel encouraged to go on, and not fight your fellow players or be envious of them over a camp BECAUSE it was rumored once within the past week, a parchment may have dropped there.<br>
<br>
It is a GAME, and you would thin Verant would remember that and lets people have fun over frustration.<br>
